    description:"These selectors directly target specific elements without depending on their relation to other elements.",
    inputCode:"<style>\r\n  \/* Type selector *\/\r\n  div {\r\n    color: blue;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  \/* Class selector *\/\r\n  .my-class {\r\n    color: green;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  \/* ID selector *\/\r\n  #unique-element {\r\n    color: red;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  \/* Universal selector *\/\r\n  * {\r\n    margin: 0;\r\n    padding: 0;\r\n  }\r\n<\/style>\r\n\r\n<div>This is a div (blue from type selector).<\/div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"my-class\">This is a paragraph with class \"my-class\" (green from class selector).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h1 id=\"unique-element\">This is an H1 with ID \"unique-element\" (red from ID selector).<\/h1>\r\n\r\n<span>This span is affected by the universal selector (no margin\/padding).<\/span>",
