    id: 27,
    title: "CSS Variables",
    description:"CSS Variables (also called Custom Properties) allow you to store reusable values and use them throughout your stylesheets. They make your CSS more maintainable, flexible, and easier to update",
    inputCode:"<style>\r\n  :root {\r\n    --primary-color: #3498db;\r\n    --secondary-color: #2ecc71;\r\n    --font-base: 16px;\r\n    --spacing-unit: 8px;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .button {\r\n    background-color: var(--primary-color);\r\n    padding: calc(var(--spacing-unit) * 2);\r\n    font-size: var(--font-base);\r\n    color: white;\r\n    border: none;\r\n    border-radius: 4px;\r\n    cursor: pointer;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .button-secondary {\r\n    background-color: var(--secondary-color);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .dark-theme {\r\n    --text-color: white;\r\n    --bg-color: #222;\r\n    background-color: var(--bg-color);\r\n    padding: 20px;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .dark-theme p {\r\n    color: var(--text-color);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .element {\r\n    width: var(--custom-width, 100%);\r\n    color: #000;\r\n    background-color: lightgray;\r\n    height: 50px;\r\n    margin-top: 10px;\r\n  }\r\n<\/style>\r\n\r\n<button class=\"button\">Primary Button<\/button>\r\n<button class=\"button button-secondary\">Secondary Button<\/button>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"dark-theme\">\r\n  <p>This paragraph is in a dark theme using custom text color.<\/p>\r\n<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"element\">Default width element (100%)<\/div>\r\n\r\n<!-- Overriding the custom width via inline style -->\r\n<div class=\"element\" style=\"--custom-width: 50%\">\r\n  Custom width element (50%)\r\n<\/div>",
