    title: "Clipping and Masking",
    description:"These techniques control which parts of an element are visible.",
    inputCode:"<style>\r\n  img {\r\n    width: 300px;\r\n    height: 200px;\r\n    object-fit: cover;\r\n    margin: 20px;\r\n    border: 4px solid #ccc;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .circle-clip {\r\n    clip-path: circle(50% at center);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .diamond-clip {\r\n    clip-path: polygon(50% 0%, 100% 50%, 50% 100%, 0% 50%);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  .masked {\r\n    mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black);\r\n    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(\r\n      to right,\r\n      transparent,\r\n      black\r\n    ); \/* for Safari *\/\r\n  }\r\n<\/style>\r\n\r\n<h2>Circular Clip<\/h2>\r\n<img src=\"https:\/\/picsum.photos\/300\/200?random=6\" alt=\"Circle\" class=\"circle-clip\" \/>\r\n\r\n<h2>Diamond Clip<\/h2>\r\n<img src=\"https:\/\/picsum.photos\/300\/200?random=7\" alt=\"Diamond\" class=\"diamond-clip\" \/>\r\n\r\n<h2>Masked (Gradient Left to Right)<\/h2>\r\n<img src=\"https:\/\/picsum.photos\/300\/200?random=8\" alt=\"Masked\" class=\"masked\" \/>",
